sti_started.Description: The starting time when the video stimulus begins to play during the scan.

sti_stopped.Description: The time when the video stimulus stops playing during the scan.

key_fix.Description: Whether the participant pressed the button when seeing 1-back. 1 indicates that the button was pressed when seeing 1-back.

levelOfOcclusion.Description: Stimulus type, where 0.1, 0.75, and 0.9 represent the image occlusion levels of 10%, 75%, and 90% respectively; n/a indicates no stimulus.

stim_file.Description: Label of the stimulus, where 0 represents aircraft A, 1 represents aircraft B, and n/a indicates no stimulus.

key_type.Description: Type of key press, where 1 indicates selecting aircraft A, 0 indicates selecting aircraft B, and n/a indicates no key press.
